Spectroscopic ellipsometry (SE) is a non-destructive test method used to analyze the optical properties of the sample. It can also deduce various information like the film thickness, crystallinity, and bandgap, depending on the modeling method41. The measured SE spectra of the TOPCon electron contact annealed at various temperatures were analyzed by the Tauc-Lorentz (T-L) dispersion model. The ε2 of T-L dispersion can be expressed as below42:7ε2(E)=0,E≤Eg\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
